description:
I am using version 1.1rc1 of ajc (AspectJ compiler). This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:
   package subpackage;
   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }
2. Compile the class using the following command: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
After executing the above command, a directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory.


Expected Behavior:
The compiled class should be placed in the existing "subpackage" directory, without creating the additional "subpackage" directory.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a class in a subpackage as described above.
2. Compile the class using the following command: ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java
